Include-tidy NEWS -- history of user-visible changes.

Copyright (C) 2026  Paul J. Lucas.
See the end of the file for license conditions.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Changes in Include-tidy 1.3

** `-h` and `-v`
Added these missing short options to `--help` output.

** Other include path options
Added support for `--include-directory-after` and `-idirafter` **clang**
options.


* Changes in Include-tidy 1.2

** Changing directory
Changing directory via the `--directory` or `-d` options now works in all
cases.

** `error`
The `--error` option is now also settable via a configuration file.

** Other include path options
Added support for `--include-directory`, `-cxx-isystem`, `-iquote`, and
`-isystem-after` **clang** options.

** `-h` and `-v`
Both are now correctly recognized as synonyms for `--help` and `--version`,
respectively.

** `=` in `-isystem`, etc.
A `=` is now correctly allowed between `-isystem` (and other include path
options) and its value, e.g., `-isystem=/path`, in addition to no `=`.


* Changes in Include-tidy 1.1.1

** Fixed cast and dereference bug
I have no idea how it never crashed without the cast and dereference.


* Changes in Include-tidy 1.1

** Printing error line
If there's an error in a source file being tidied, **include-tidy** now prints
the offending line with a `^` at the offending column.

** Better invocation from Makefile
A better way to invoke **include-tidy** from a Makefile is now given.

** `--comment-style` help default
Added `default="//"` to the help message for `--comment-style`.

** `--comment-style` implies `--all-includes`
Use of the `--comment-style` option now implies the `--all-includes` option.

** New `--comment-symbols` option
A new `--comment-symbols` or `-S` option allows you to specify the sort order
of symbols in comments: `alpha` (alphabetically, the default), `length` (name
length), `ref-count` (reference count, descending), `most-used` (only the most-
used symbol).

** Man page fixes
A few things on the man page were fixed.


* Changes in Include-tidy 1.0

** Initial version.

